{"content": "By Gregory Piatetsky , KDnuggets. Glassdoor, a popular job site, again published a list of \r 50 Best Jobs in America , \r and in 2018, for the third year in a row, Data Scientist ranked as \r the no. 1 job. Data Scientist had an overall Job score 4.8 out of 5,\r $110,000 Median Base Salary, and over 4,000 job openings on Glassdoor.\r \r In 2017,\r \r Glassdoor also ranked Data Scientist as the best job in America ,\r with the same job score and the same median base salary, but slightly higher job satisfaction. \r In 2016, \r \r Glassdoor ranked Data Scientist as no. 1 job in USA for the first time, with median salary $117K, and about 1,700 jobs listed. \r \r Here are the top 5 jobs in 2018 and also other jobs in top 50 related to Analytics, Big Data, Data Science, according to Glassdoor:\r 2018 Rank Job Title Job Score Job Satisfaction Median Base Salary Job Openings 1 Data Scientist 4.8 4.2 $110,000 4,524 2 DevOps Engineer 4.6 4.0 $105,000 3,369 3 Marketing Manager 4.6 4.0 $85,000 6,439 4 Occupational Therapist 4.5 4.0 $74,000 11,903 5 HR Manager 4.5 3.9 $85,000 4,458 18 Analytics Manager 4.4 3.9 $115,000 1,381 26 Database Administrator 4.3 3.8 $94,000 2,370 33 Data Engineer 4.2 3.7 $100,000 2,816 38 Data Analyst 4.2 3.9 $60,000 4,729 \r Compared to 2017 ranking, \r Data Engineer dropped from n. 3 to n. 33, \r Analytics Manager dropped from n. 5 to n. 18, and \r Database Administrator dropped from n. 7 to n. 26.\r \r Perhaps the decline in job satisfaction across the number of jobs in reflected in growing demand for the job of Occupational Therapist, which jumped from n. 12 to n. 4 job in 2018?\r \r Note that Data Scientist and Machine Learning engineer were also\r \r top US emerging jobs , according to LinkedIn.\r \r You can also reach those talented but hard-to-find Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers by placing a \r \r job ad on KDnuggets - email to \r .\r See Details and posting info .\r Related: Machine Learning Engineer, Data Scientis